Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @sweet potato{300%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and sprinkle over half the @dried thyme{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{20-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}(thinly sliced).

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Zest then squeeze the juice from the @lime{1}.

Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

== Stew ==

Place a large #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the scallion (keeping a little aside for garnish). Season with salt and pepper and fry, stirring occasionally, until soft and sweet, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @chorizo{100%g} and bell pepper. Fry for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @garam masala{1%sachet} and remaining thyme. Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @chopped tomatoes{1%pack}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet}, @coconut milk{1%pack} and @water{100%ml}. IMPORTANT: Cook chorizo thoroughly.

Bring the stew to the boil.

Cover the pot and simmer on low heat for ~{12-15%minutes}.

With 5 mins of cooking time left, add the kidney beans to the pot.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Remove the pot from the heat.

Stir in the roasted sweet potato.

Add half the lime juice.

Divide the chorizo and sweet potato stew between #bowls{}.

Garnish with the lime zest and reserved scallion.

Finish with a splash of lime juice to taste.